<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03080e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03080e">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03080e"> 80(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Interpreter / &mdash; Maam <font face="wake">+</font> </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: This may refer to the trial of the peasant seventy-year-old Myles Joyce for murders committed in Maamtrasna in the west of Ireland. As Joyce spoke only Irish, the court had recourse to an interpreter. The cross-examination was at times comic; at times tragic. The simple-minded Joyce, who was manifestly innocent, was (scandalously) found guilty as he was unable to comprehend the trial itself, much less defend himself. </mm> </dd></dl>
